{
  "text": "On the other hand, because P 1 k n HC ik;n M 2 kj;n = 1(i = j) by construction, part (b) implies that HC n is consistent provided k HC n k 1 = O p (1): A simple condition for this to occur can be stated in terms of M n : Indeed, if M n < 1=2; then HC n is diagonally dominant and it follows from Theorem 1 of [CITATION_1] that",
